1
00:00:11,050 --> 00:00:14,240
♫ When romance is too insignificant ♫

2
00:00:14,240 --> 00:00:21,670
♫ But I can't stop missing you, like a bad cold ♫

3
00:00:21,670 --> 00:00:28,460
♫ Drifting in a deserted island, where feelings have no reception ♫

4
00:00:28,460 --> 00:00:32,180
♫ Have you been well? ♫

5
00:00:32,180 --> 00:00:36,250
♫ Don't worry, I'll be fine ♫

6
00:00:36,250 --> 00:00:39,400
♫ Don't worry, I can't fall asleep ♫

7
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:46,960
♫ Don't worry, I can't get used to this lonely world ♫

8
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:53,740
♫ Hitting the pause button, leaving your side ♫

9
00:00:53,740 --> 00:01:00,810
♫ Letting the memories migrate to that day of happiness ♫

10
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:07,010
♫ I'm trying hard to smile as I say goodbye to you ♫

11
00:01:07,010 --> 00:01:13,000
♫ I recall and long for the happiness you want, I can make it happen ♫

12
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,130
♫ Can't hold back the tears, leading to regret ♫

13
00:01:16,130 --> 00:01:22,140
♫ Losing you whom I love, heartbreak is inevitable ♫

14
00:01:22,140 --> 00:01:28,660
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

15
00:01:28,660 --> 00:01:31,640
[Lost Romance]

16
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:35,130
My childhood seems to have been deleted completely

17
00:01:35,130 --> 00:01:36,790
with the press of a button today.

18
00:01:36,790 --> 00:01:39,470
Because as long as there's still someone in this world

19
00:01:39,470 --> 00:01:41,050
who remembers those things,

20
00:01:41,050 --> 00:01:43,880
your childhood will never be erased.

21
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:46,240
Don't be so nice to me. Don't make me confused.

22
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:48,460
Don't make me fall in love with you.

23
00:01:48,460 --> 00:01:49,760
You've done so much for me,

24
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:52,760
and now you're telling me that you don't want to fall in love with me?

25
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:55,280
You don't love me? Then let me love you.

26
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:57,350
Hu Chaoqin knows our weaknesses too well.

27
00:01:57,350 --> 00:01:59,240
First, he eliminated you, the hardest to deal with.

28
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:01,250
Then he had Tianjian and me fight against each other.

29
00:02:01,250 --> 00:02:03,120
Lastly, he got rid of Tianjian.

30
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:06,200
I will learn to not be so self-righteous

31
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:08,330
and think that I can do everything.

32
00:02:08,330 --> 00:02:11,720
But now we still have the opportunity to find our true selves.

33
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:14,560
At least I hope to have the opportunity

34
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:18,080
to be a good role model for Tianjian as his sister.

35
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:20,400
Nothing came out of the auditing we did earlier.

36
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:22,550
Director Hu is more cautious than we thought.

37
00:02:22,550 --> 00:02:25,090
Zheng Xiao'en, I'd like your help with something.

38
00:02:25,090 --> 00:02:28,260
He Tianxing and Situ Aoran are like a loop.

39
00:02:28,260 --> 00:02:30,370
Maybe I’m projecting my feelings,

40
00:02:30,370 --> 00:02:33,400
so I’m treating He Tianxing as Situ Aoran.

41
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:36,390
I should let go and keep moving forward.

42
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:39,640
Zheng Xiao'en, am I, He Tianxing, someone you can toy with?

43
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:43,880
I'm certain that you have feelings for me.

44
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:48,630
To be honest, I had feelings for you before.

45
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:51,730
But I can't go beyond liking.

46
00:02:56,640 --> 00:03:02,330
[Lost Romance]

47
00:03:02,330 --> 00:03:05,120
[The Final Chapter]
[The Twilight Breaking Dawn]

48
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:07,950
[Incoming Call: Sorry, I'm Married]

49
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:17,520
Then where's your husband?

50
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:19,740
Every time something happens,

51
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:22,970
why is it only your coworker by your side?

52
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:27,000
He's not here anymore.

53
00:03:30,610 --> 00:03:33,730
It's not what you think.

54
00:03:33,730 --> 00:03:39,120
In short, he's somewhere very far away.

55
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,990
When is he coming back?

56
00:03:45,810 --> 00:03:47,980
So you guys are separated?

57
00:03:52,550 --> 00:03:54,650
Then what's the problem?

58
00:03:54,650 --> 00:03:56,160
How can you think there's no problem?

59
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:58,770
I... I've gotten married.

60
00:03:58,770 --> 00:04:01,500
You're single right now, and I'm single too.

61
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:03,970
So the problem is...?

62
00:04:06,010 --> 00:04:08,150
The problem is

63
00:04:09,170 --> 00:04:13,740
I'm not ready to love someone again.

64
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:21,560
Then when will you be ready?

65
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:26,300
Did you think that after hearing your reason,

66
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:31,320
I was just going to say "I understand" and then quietly leave?

67
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:36,840
- I—
- You truly underestimate me.

68
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:38,940
Then what exactly do you want me to do?

69
00:04:38,940 --> 00:04:40,930
Take a good look at your feelings deep inside.

70
00:04:40,930 --> 00:04:42,950
No running away.

71
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:46,200
That's impossible.

72
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:50,520
It's possible, because I will make you forget him.

73
00:04:52,190 --> 00:04:57,550
It's so wonderful to have you in this world.

74
00:04:58,550 --> 00:05:01,000
I love you.

75
00:05:01,670 --> 00:05:03,990
I will love you forever.

76
00:05:09,230 --> 00:05:12,020
Make me forget him?

77
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:17,370
Someone else might be able to,

78
00:05:17,370 --> 00:05:19,910
but you're the only one who can't.

79
00:05:21,390 --> 00:05:23,940
Why can't I?

80
00:05:31,050 --> 00:05:34,600
Since you can't give me a reason, then that means I still have a chance.

81
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:36,890
I might as well tell you this now.

82
00:05:36,890 --> 00:05:41,710
I'm the kind of person who doesn't give up easily once I decide to do something.

83
00:05:41,710 --> 00:05:43,570
He Tianxing.

84
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:48,030
I won't waver.

85
00:05:48,940 --> 00:05:51,000
Don't waste your time.

86
00:05:53,150 --> 00:05:55,550
That is my business.

87
00:05:55,550 --> 00:06:00,580
Don't make things hard on yourself for someone else.

88
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:09,730
It's not someone else... it's you.

89
00:06:09,730 --> 00:06:13,760
♫ I lost to you ♫

90
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:22,900
♫ All of the innocent romance was lost to you ♫

91
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:26,520
♫ If you were a painter ♫

92
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,970
♫ Then I'll be your canvas ♫

93
00:06:28,970 --> 00:06:32,660
♫ Oh, lost to you ♫

94
00:06:32,660 --> 00:06:34,740
Why?

95
00:06:34,740 --> 00:06:37,080
Why can't we report Hu Chaoqin to the police

96
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:39,190
when we know that he's laundering money by using artwork?

97
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:41,490
It's useless to report it to the police.

98
00:06:41,490 --> 00:06:44,880
- Why is it useless?
- Because it's not illegal.

99
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:47,120
It's not illegal?

100
00:06:55,910 --> 00:06:58,020
I'll sell this piece to you.

101
00:07:00,580 --> 00:07:02,490
NT$800 million (~US$27.9 million).

102
00:07:03,150 --> 00:07:05,350
NT$800 million?

103
00:07:05,350 --> 00:07:06,760
Am I crazy?

104
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:09,780
Why would I spend NT$800 million to buy a piece of scrap paper?

105
00:07:11,620 --> 00:07:13,880
Antiques and works of art do not have fixed prices.

106
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:16,580
They just need someone willing to sell and someone willing to buy.

107
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:19,600
As long as someone is willing to pay for it,

108
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:23,520
this scrap of paper is worth NT$800 million.

109
00:07:26,770 --> 00:07:30,370
Unless we can find his secret bank account

110
00:07:30,370 --> 00:07:32,920
to prove that the money went into his pockets,

111
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:35,990
even the police wouldn't be able to do anything.

112
00:07:38,730 --> 00:07:40,830
Hu Chaoqin is so cautious.

113
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:43,750
He wouldn't reveal his whereabouts so easily.

114
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:48,480
So it's not surprising that the boss of the art gallery has never seen him before.

115
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:53,000
Do you have an idea?

116
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,600
Since the boss of the art gallery has not met the old fox,

117
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:58,420
that give us space to maneuver.

118
00:08:00,710 --> 00:08:02,500
Let's take a gamble.

119
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:10,820
[Tianliang Group]

120
00:08:10,820 --> 00:08:15,670
Miss, we must hurry with the matter on re-electing members of the board of directors.

121
00:08:16,550 --> 00:08:20,500
I know. I'm already setting it up in secret.

122
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,870
Some things can't be rushed.

123
00:08:23,690 --> 00:08:27,980
Now that the opportunity is on your side,

124
00:08:27,980 --> 00:08:30,950
you must hold on to it.

125
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:34,540
I will.

126
00:08:34,540 --> 00:08:36,520
Leave the matter regarding the board of directors to me.

127
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:39,620
Don't worry, Uncle Hu. I'll do it quickly.

128
00:08:39,620 --> 00:08:41,560
Okay.

129
00:08:43,510 --> 00:08:45,040
Excuse me.

130
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:49,490
Miss, the commission has been deposited into your account.

131
00:08:49,490 --> 00:08:51,650
Please confirm this.

132
00:08:56,660 --> 00:09:00,070
[Deposited: NT$30,000,000.00]

133
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:03,530
All it took was my signature to receive this?

134
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:08,430
NT$30 million (~US$1 million), not one cent missing.

135
00:09:08,430 --> 00:09:12,990
It's as I said, a guaranteed profit with no losses.

136
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:17,920
[Qiaozhi: The old fox ordered flowers again.]

137
00:09:29,890 --> 00:09:32,190
I want to sell a chess set.

138
00:09:42,970 --> 00:09:47,330
I said I wanted to sell a chess set, and he gave me this without saying a word.

139
00:09:47,330 --> 00:09:51,140
It was as we thought. Delivering flowers was a signal.

140
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:08,340
No wonder we couldn't find his personal account.

141
00:10:08,340 --> 00:10:10,370
Thank you.

142
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,790
Excuse me.

143
00:10:15,410 --> 00:10:16,970
Hello?

144
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:19,790
It was already taken away?

145
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:25,220
What do you mean?

146
00:10:25,220 --> 00:10:27,170
What?

147
00:10:27,170 --> 00:10:30,040
Wait for me at our usual place.

148
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:33,130
Miss, sorry, I've got to go.

149
00:10:33,130 --> 00:10:35,180
What's wrong? Did something happen?

150
00:10:35,180 --> 00:10:36,900
Sorry.

151
00:11:01,610 --> 00:11:03,320
What are you doing?

152
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:05,210
What do you think you're doing?

153
00:11:11,830 --> 00:11:14,320
I don't know what you're looking for.

154
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:48,800
There is nothing. If there is nothing else, I'll be going back to my office for work.

155
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,720
Please do as you wish.

156
00:11:54,210 --> 00:11:55,880
Wait.

157
00:12:45,270 --> 00:12:48,820
So all of the money that Tianliang lost is here.

158
00:12:50,170 --> 00:12:55,260
Uncle Hu, as the funds flowed out of Tianliang into unknown companies,

159
00:12:55,260 --> 00:12:59,610
did you happily accept sum after sum?

160
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:03,750
If you return the money now,

161
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:05,650
we don't have to investigate this matter any further.

162
00:13:05,650 --> 00:13:07,930
Investigate it.

163
00:13:07,930 --> 00:13:10,240
He Tianxing, even if you had heavenly powers,

164
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:12,980
you wouldn't be able to find anything.

165
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:15,560
You're not afraid that we'll report to the police?

166
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,830
Everything I've done is legal.

167
00:13:17,830 --> 00:13:20,110
Besides, Tianjian was the one who signed the contract.

168
00:13:20,110 --> 00:13:23,220
How has the He family ever wronged you?

169
00:13:26,370 --> 00:13:31,050
Thirty years. Thirty years!

170
00:13:31,050 --> 00:13:34,770
For thirty years, I worked myself to the bone for Tianliang, and what did I get?

171
00:13:35,410 --> 00:13:39,200
Thirty years ago, when Tianliang had just gotten started,

172
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,220
He Zhaonan put in the money, but I put in the effort.

173
00:13:41,220 --> 00:13:44,830
And bit by bit, we grew Tianliang Group to what it is now.

174
00:13:45,680 --> 00:13:47,760
But what have I gained?

175
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:49,440
They guarded against me like they would guard against a thief.

176
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:51,870
Not even a single stock was given to me.

177
00:13:51,870 --> 00:13:53,950
Before He Zhaonan left,

178
00:13:53,950 --> 00:13:58,230
he still wanted me to continue assisting He Tianxing.

179
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:05,180
Your family wants to treat me like your dog?!

180
00:14:06,630 --> 00:14:10,250
You know, in my eyes, the three of you

181
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:13,440
don't have a single redeeming feature except for your surname He.

182
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,930
If the three of you didn't have seeds of betrayal in your hearts,

183
00:14:15,930 --> 00:14:17,330
no matter how much I watered it,

184
00:14:17,330 --> 00:14:19,860
not a single evil flower would ever bloom within you.

185
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:23,130
That's right, I want He Zhaonan to know that

186
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:25,550
handing this company over to the Hes

187
00:14:25,550 --> 00:14:27,970
is a wrong decision beyond all reason!

188
00:14:27,970 --> 00:14:29,170
Hu Chaoqin!

189
00:14:29,170 --> 00:14:31,320
He Tianxing, what are you doing?

190
00:14:36,830 --> 00:14:42,170
Uncle Hu, seeing as you've worked so hard for the He family for the past thirty years,

191
00:14:43,330 --> 00:14:45,020
just leave.

192
00:14:46,310 --> 00:14:49,760
He Tianxing, are you crazy? How can you just let him leave?

193
00:14:51,730 --> 00:14:54,160
You're not playing any tricks?

194
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:56,010
No tricks.

195
00:15:00,350 --> 00:15:01,740
What are you doing?!

196
00:15:01,740 --> 00:15:03,560
You just let him leave?

197
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:06,360
He almost destroyed the entire Tianliang.

198
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,050
I've already handed the bag of diamonds

199
00:15:13,050 --> 00:15:15,630
and the rest of the evidence we've collected to the police.

200
00:15:18,710 --> 00:15:22,020
To him, I couldn't say too much.

201
00:15:22,020 --> 00:15:26,120
Because Tianliang does owe him.

202
00:15:26,770 --> 00:15:29,320
But he committed a crime,

203
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:32,010
and he'll have to pay for that in the end.

204
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:41,470
Help me pack my luggage and passport.

205
00:15:41,470 --> 00:15:43,770
I have to leave the country for few days.

206
00:15:43,770 --> 00:15:46,000
Okay. Good.

207
00:16:01,830 --> 00:16:04,830
[Police]

208
00:16:10,190 --> 00:16:12,220
Tianjian.

209
00:16:16,090 --> 00:16:19,280
Mom, don't be sad.

210
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:22,250
It's not like I'll be jailed forever.

211
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:25,300
Also, once I get out,

212
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:27,430
I can do things with both feet on the ground.

213
00:16:27,430 --> 00:16:29,910
That's good, isn't it?

214
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:35,290
During this time, you have to stay strong.

215
00:16:39,770 --> 00:16:41,620
What are you doing?

216
00:16:43,610 --> 00:16:47,300
Sometimes, being a strong woman may not be a good thing.

217
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:50,970
This is what I learned in life.

218
00:16:50,970 --> 00:16:53,710
If you don't force me to be a strong woman,

219
00:16:53,710 --> 00:16:58,160
I won't force you to be a little woman anymore.

220
00:16:58,160 --> 00:17:01,370
When you come out,

221
00:17:01,370 --> 00:17:04,530
I will definitely learn how to respect you.

222
00:17:06,430 --> 00:17:08,290
Do not cry in front of me.

223
00:17:08,290 --> 00:17:10,310
I won't.

224
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:16,650
You.

225
00:17:16,650 --> 00:17:18,590
Yes?

226
00:17:23,060 --> 00:17:25,020
I'm leaving my mom in your care.

227
00:17:25,020 --> 00:17:27,210
Do not worry, Miss.

228
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:30,020
Thanks.

229
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,880
I've always wanted to say "thanks" to you.

230
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:37,890
All this time, you have been doing everything you could to help me.

231
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:40,960
It's just that I've never been able to find the right time.

232
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:43,950
Thank you.

233
00:17:49,030 --> 00:17:51,200
This is my duty.

234
00:18:00,830 --> 00:18:02,990
We need to go in.

235
00:18:19,020 --> 00:18:24,720
Hello, everyone. I am Tianliang Group's new chairman, He Tianxing.

236
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:28,300
First, I want to send my sincerest apologies regarding the recent crises

237
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:35,110
to all the employees, investors, and others who care for Tianliang.

238
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:53,180
Tianliang Group has decided to move forward with a strategic HR adjustment

239
00:18:53,180 --> 00:18:55,550
in order to implement favorable resignation and retirement plans.

240
00:18:55,550 --> 00:18:59,480
Also, regarding the capital losses caused by wrong decisions,

241
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:01,580
in addition to negotiating with bank groups,

242
00:19:01,580 --> 00:19:05,180
we also plan to use the skills we have to attract foreign investors.

243
00:19:05,180 --> 00:19:08,630
Within the company, we also want to change the management system

244
00:19:08,630 --> 00:19:10,520
and explore the talent we have internally.

245
00:19:10,520 --> 00:19:14,260
We will train professional managers to straighten out our problems arising from

246
00:19:14,260 --> 00:19:17,950
the cross-shareholding of our hospitality, real estate, and financial institutions.

247
00:19:17,950 --> 00:19:19,720
CEO.

248
00:19:21,180 --> 00:19:24,790
My stomach hurts. Accompany me to the restroom.

249
00:19:24,790 --> 00:19:26,710
Let's go.

250
00:19:26,710 --> 00:19:28,740
You've just returned to the company,

251
00:19:28,740 --> 00:19:31,370
and the company already seems like a whole new place.

252
00:19:31,370 --> 00:19:36,210
I believe that the company will only improve from now on.

253
00:19:36,210 --> 00:19:37,350
Thank you.

254
00:19:37,350 --> 00:19:39,600
After the company affairs have come to an end,

255
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:41,550
does that mean there will be time

256
00:19:41,550 --> 00:19:44,410
for us to watch the sunrise together?

257
00:19:46,630 --> 00:19:48,380
Ling Chuchu.

258
00:19:49,020 --> 00:19:52,800
